title: Rabbit Ears
json: {u'Plot': u'Meet Dan and Jeff - young and effervescent 30-somethings making their way in a no-nonsense, play-by-the-rules, anything-goes small rural big city town. Between scraping pennies together and entertaining their unusual friends Duffy, Wyatt and the neighbor Vicky, they find just enough time in their busy schedules to not pay their cable bill. title: Live with Lori
json: {u'Plot': u'Live with Lori is a cross between a Political News show and a Traditional Cooking show. Each week host Lori Halbert serves up a little "Political Food for Thought" as she interviews politicians from all across Florida, while teaching them how to prepare a delicious meal. So, who are the people writing the laws for our state, and our county? How do they feel about their service, their duty to us, the toll it takes on their families, their jobs and their lives? It was with these questions in mind, I set myself to find a way to present an elected official in a manner in which everyone can relate, and to combine my love of cooking with what I learned in the kitchens across my district to present my audience with the real people who serve them in public office. Food is truly the "great uniter". Everyone must eat, and someone must prepare it, so what better way to get to know someone than in the kitchen? I find this to be the perfect setting since the kitchen is the heart of the home, where families gather, take nourishment, and make their own decisions for their future. This is not a show to promote my beliefs or my agenda. It is a non-partisan show that will allow a hungry public to draw their own conclusions about the real people who serve as their elected officials. Viewers will have a chance to learn a new recipe, and perhaps come away with a new taste for how their government works and realizing the person working for them in office is just like you and me, with hopes and dreams not that different from our own.', u'Rated': u'N/A', u'Title': u'Live with Lori', u'Ratings': [], u'Writer': u'Lori Halbert', u'Actors': u'Lori Halbert', u'Type': u'series', u'imdbVotes': u'N/A', u'totalSeasons': u'1', u'Poster': u'N/A', u'Director': u'N/A', u'Released': u'04 Oct 2012', u'Awards': u'N/A', u'Genre': u'Talk-Show', u'Response': u'True', u'Language': u'English', u'Country': u'USA', u'Runtime': u'N/A', u'imdbID': u'tt2501364', u'Metascore': u'N/A', u'imdbRating': u'N/A', u'Year': u'2012\u2013'}

title: Revolution
json: {u'Plot': u"Our entire way of life depends on electricity. So what would happen if it just stopped working? Well, one day, like a switch turned off, the world is suddenly thrust back into the dark ages. Planes fall from the sky, hospitals shut down, and communication is impossible. And without any modern technology, who can tell us why? Now, 15 years later, life is back to what it once was long before the industrial revolution: families living in quiet cul-de-sacs, and when the sun goes down lanterns and candles are lit. title: Testing Milton Friedman
json: {u'Plot': u"2012 is the 100th anniversary of Milton Friedman's birth. His work and ideas continue to make the world a better place. As part of Milton Friedman's Century, the ideas featured in the landmark television series Free To Choose are being revisited in a new 3-part PBS broadcast. Testing Milton Friedman, hosted by award-winning veteran journalist Emily Rooney with a distinguished panel of two Friedman advocates and two challengers, presents a lively discussion and debate on Friedman's still-provocative ideas in each of these hour-long programs. Special emphasis is placed on the relevance of his ideas in view of the current world economic situation. The episodes are as follows: Equality of Opportunity - the panelists explore Friedman's ideas and the possible implications of equality of opportunity and equality of outcome. The panelists include: Walter Williams - author, syndicated columnist, and the John M. Olin Distinguished Professor of Economics at George Mason University; Shikha Dalmia - senior policy analyst at Reason Foundation; Matthew Yglesias - political blogger; John Bouman - president and advocacy director of the Sargent Shriver National Center on Poverty Law. Government Control - a discussion of what can occur when legislators, often in collusion with big business, intervene in the market. This program features: Amity Shlaes - author and syndicated columnist and a director at the George W. Bush Institute; Bryan Caplan - professor of economics at George Mason University, research fellow at the Mercatus Center and author; Austan Goolsbee - former chief economist for President Obama's Economic Recovery Advisory Board, a member of the Obama cabinet and professor of economics at the University of Chicago's Booth School of Business; Clarence Page - Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist from the Chicago Tribune. Free Markets - the panel discusses the classic explanations and demonstrations of the workings and benefits of a free market and economic freedom. The panelists are: Kevin Murphy - George J. Stigler Professor of Economics at the University of Chicago and a senior fellow at the Hoover Institution; Raghuram Rajan - Eric J. Gleacher Professor of Finance at the University of Chicago's Booth School of Business and an economic advisor to the Prime Minister of India; Dani Rodrik - author and professor of international political economy at Harvard's Kennedy School of Government; Brad DeLong - professor of economics at the University of California at Berkeley and Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Treasury in the Clinton administration.", u'Rated': u'N/A', u'Title': u'Testing Milton Friedman', u'Ratings': [], u'Writer': u'N/A', u'Actors': u'Emily Rooney', u'Type': u'series', u'imdbVotes': u'N/A', u'totalSeasons': u'N/A', u'Poster': u'N/A', u'Director': u'N/A', u'Released': u'02 Sep 2012', u'Awards': u'N/A', u'Genre': u'Documentary', u'Response': u'True', u'Language': u'English', u'Country': u'USA', u'Runtime': u'N/A', u'imdbID': u'tt3352402', u'Metascore': u'N/A', u'imdbRating': u'N/A', u'Year': u'2012\u2013'}

title: Go Public: A Documentary Film Project
json: {u'Plot': u"Go Public: A Day in the Life of PUSD will be a two-hour video document of one entire day in the Pasadena Unified School District. Pasadena is a racially and economically diverse community in Southern California with 28 public school campuses. Go Public will tell the story of one full day from sun up to long after sundown. Public education is a privilege and a right available to everyone in our country and 90% of the nations' children attend public school. We want to provide a window into the world of one urban school district, the many dedicated people, the myriad of opportunities available and the complexity of effectively serving the needs of all students. On May 8, 2012, fifty small camera crews followed a wide-ranging group of individuals who participate, attend, support and work in the School District. Teachers, students, principals, volunteers and many others revealed their unique involvement in what makes a public school district function. This film will be the story of public school at the moment things are happening. No voice-over narrative and no expert commentaries. By filming over one complete day, we had access to the struggles and resolutions that often occur many times in an average day. Through personal stories, Go Public will be a film that articulates the experiences of navigating a typical day in public school. This project is important now because too much focus has been placed on what is broken in public school education. There is room for improvement, but we also want to capture the good things that go on every day in our public schools, the teamwork it takes and the textured richness for those involved. By telling the stories of individuals that work and participate in the schools, we will encourage viewers to become informed and compassionate advocates for their community public schools.", u'Rated': u'N/A', u'Title': u'Go Public: A Documentary Film Project', u'Ratings': [], u'Writer': u'N/A', u'Actors': u'Jodie West', u'Type': u'series', u'imdbVotes': u'N/A', u'totalSeasons': u'N/A', u'Poster': u'http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTU1MTU3NjAxMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMDU4ODc2OQ@@._V1_SX300.jpg', u'Director': u'N/A', u'Released': u'15 Aug 2012', u'Awards': u'N/A', u'Genre': u'Documentary', u'Response': u'True', u'Language': u'English', u'Country': u'USA', u'Runtime': u'N/A', u'imdbID': u'tt2381118', u'Metascore': u'N/A', u'imdbRating': u'N/A', u'Year': u'2012\u2013'}

title: Walking in LA
json: {u'Plot': u"A comedic web series about the totally broke, totally car-less and the totally awesome. Dumped by his rich girlfriend and fired from the mail room at her father's law firm on the same day, Keith suddenly finds himself holed up in a tiny bachelor apartment, forced to fend for himself in the city of Los Angeles. Out of loneliness, desperation and pure boredom, Keith decides to shoot a web Vlog to document his attempts at getting himself together. Through the magic of craigslist, he enlists the talents of James (an inept yet overly confident, womanizing cameraman) to help him shoot this epic adventure. Step one in Keith's quest to become a fully functioning human being is to lay out a plan: 1.Get a job. 2. Get a car. 3. Get a cool girlfriend. But, as he ventures out in the city, he quickly realizes there are many obstacles standing between him and self actualization: Hard boiled cops obsessed with dealing out jaywalking tickets. Self important skinny-jean wearing hipsters who guard their turf with an iron fist and an ironic t-shirt. Tweaked out whack-a-doos who ride the #4 bus after midnight... and many more. In order to beat the odds, Keith will have to keep his wits about him and make the most of every available resource. No-one makes it alone in LA, and in Keith's case his allies come in the form of the fellow losers and underdogs of the city, whose assistance is often a double-edged sword.", u'Rated': u'N/A', u'Title': u'Walking in LA', u'Ratings': [{u'Source': u'Internet Movie Database', u'Value': u'6.8/10'}], u'Writer': u'N/A', u'Actors': u'Keith Jordan, Taryn Southern, Chris Jorie, Christian Calloway', u'Type': u'series', u'imdbVotes': u'9', u'totalSeasons': u'N/A', u'Poster': u'http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTY3MDQ3NTI4OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwOTk4NzIyOA@@._V1_SX300.jpg', u'Director': u'N/A', u'Released': u'18 Jul 2012', u'Awards': u'N/A', u'Genre': u'Comedy', u'Response': u'True', u'Language': u'English', u'Country': u'USA', u'Runtime': u'57 min', u'imdbID': u'tt2305868', u'Metascore': u'N/A', u'imdbRating': u'6.8', u'Year': u'2012\u2013'}

title: Renman Music and Business
json: {u'Plot': u'Steve Rennie, longtime manager of Incubus and a driving force behind the band\'s multi-platinum commercial success, has launched Renmanmb.com, an online gathering place for musicians and music professionals trying to \'break in\' to the business. Full of exclusive content and video, the site is home to Rennie\'s weekly web show Renman MB Live where aspiring artists gain "insider access" to the music industry. Each week, Rennie opens his office doors to aspiring artists from different musical genres, giving them his no-holds-barred feedback on what they are doing right - and wrong - on their journey to success.
